cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ITU and Cosmology: A Single-Axiom View of Big Bang, Inflation, Dark Matter, Dark Energy, Hubble/S_8 Tensions, CMB B-modes, Cosmic Horizons, and the 2026-2050 Observational Roadmap"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Terada
    given-names: Munehiro
    affiliation: Roboken
    email: munehiro.terada@roboken2.com
abstract: >
  We apply the Information-Theoretic Unification (ITU) framework
  (Terada 2026, concept DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20109209; current latest
  Tier 0 v3.0 at 10.5281/zenodo.20200156) to cosmology. This is
  Tier 1 paper #19, the third paper of Block A (Physics/Math
  deepening) and dual specialization of Tier 1 #17 Quantum Gravity
  (DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20230667) and #18 Black Holes (DOI 10.5281/
  zenodo.20233070), completing the HORIZON TRIAD with K_cosmic
  (observer INSIDE de Sitter horizon). The ITU polytope reaches
  19 vertices with Tier 1 #19 attaining degree 18 (new max).
  Pass-1 progress: 134 of 220 phases (60.9%).
  Phase 127 establishes Big Bang ΛCDM. Friedmann equations
  integrate to age 13.80 Gyr (Planck 2018: 13.797 Gyr). Planck
  parameters H_0 = 67.4 km/s/Mpc, Ω_m = 0.315, Ω_Λ = 0.685.
  de Sitter horizon r_dS = 5.37 Gpc, S_dS = 3.31e+122 nats.
  Phase 128 covers inflation. Slow-roll for V = (1/2)m²φ²:
  n_s = 0.965 matched at φ = 15.11 M_Pl, r ≈ 0.14 (EXCLUDED).
  Surviving models: Starobinsky R² (r ≈ 0.003), Higgs, hilltop.
  Phase 129 covers DM + structure. Milky Way rotation v_total
  = 216 km/s ≈ observed; Ω_DM = 0.265. DM candidates span 53
  orders of magnitude. S_8 tension 3.69σ (CMB vs lensing).
  Phase 130 covers DE + Λ problem. SNe Ia at z=0.5: Δμ = 0.39
  mag indicates accelerating expansion. Λ problem: theoretical
  ρ_vac ~10^120 times observed (Weinberg 1989). CKN holographic
  bound reduces to ~10^17. DESI Y1: w_0 = -0.95, w_a = -0.39
  (2-4σ ΛCDM deviation).
  Phase 131 deepens tensions. Hubble: late 73.91 ± 0.90 vs
  early 67.92 ± 0.30, combined tension 6.30σ. S_8: CMB 0.837
  vs lensing 0.773, tension 3.69σ. EDE alone worsens S_8;
  compounded EDE + Interacting DM resolves both. ITU K-state
  superposition naturally accommodates.
  Phase 132 covers CMB E/B polarization. E-mode acoustic
  peaks at ℓ~140. B-mode primordial bumps at ℓ ~ 5 (reion) +
  ℓ ~ 100 (recomb); lensing peak ℓ ~ 1000. LiteBIRD (2032)
  targets r ~ 0.001 (5σ at r ≥ 0.005). r = 0.001 corresponds
  to V^{1/4} = 5.6e+15 GeV (near GUT).
  Phase 133 covers cosmic horizons + multiverse. Particle
  horizon 46.95 Gly, event 17.53 Gly (= de Sitter), Hubble
  14.51 Gly. S_dS = 3.31e+122 nats = observable universe info
  cap. Tegmark Level I-IV mapped to ITU K-state realization
  space; string landscape ~10^500 vacua.
  Phase 134 integrates under K_cosmic. 19-vertex polytope:
  111 edges, ⟨k⟩ = 11.68. Strong couplings: #17 QG (0.95),
  #18 BH (0.85), #10 Energy (0.80). Horizon TRIAD #17 (general)
  → #18 (BH inside) + #19 (cosmic inside) form inside/outside
  dual specialization pair. Ten falsifiable predictions for
  2026-2050: LiteBIRD r ~ 0.001 detected 2034 P=0.85, Hubble
  >6σ confirmed 2027 P=0.80, DESI evolving DE 2027 P=0.75,
  S_8 >4σ 2030 P=0.70, CMB-S4 2035 P=0.60, PBH DM 2038 P=0.55,
  EDE+IDM ΛCDM replacement 2035 P=0.55, anthropic Λ 2040
  P=0.45, LiteBIRD τ 2034 P=0.75, multiverse Level II 2050
  P=0.30. Grand P_avg = 0.630. Strong/Medium/Weak = 6/3/1.
  Central thesis: ITU axiom dS = d<K> specializes to K_cosmic
  at cosmological horizons, unifying Big Bang ΛCDM, inflation,
  DM, DE, Hubble+S_8 tensions, CMB B-modes, multiverse, and
  holographic information bound under one principle. Block A
  papers 1-3 (#17 QG + #18 BH + #19 Cosmology) form HORIZON
  TRIAD. LiteBIRD (2034) and DESI Y3 (2027) provide strongest
  near-term tests. Pass-1 interpretive synthesis; numerical
  results agree with established literature.
